<subSubSection pageId="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[272,801,1150,1731]" pageId="4">DIAGNOSIS: Cephalon broader than long, with posterior border slightly concave. Composite glabellar lobe short and broad, round­ ed anteriorly, flattened dorsally, with moderate inclination anteriorly. Glabellar surface ornamentated with low, rounded tubercles, each one somewhat separated from the others, and gradually diminishing in size anteriorly. Occipital ring without spines or tubercles. Genal angles rounded. Eyes with 13 or 14 dorsoventral files, with 3 or 4 lenses per file. Visual surface convex, raised somewhat above glabellar level.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
